## 3. The Two-Layer Identity Model

v0.4 results establish a clear two-layer structure:

### Layer A — Statistical Anomaly Detection

Statistical metrics detect structural attackers reliably.

An attacker without access to internal state produces trajectories
with near-zero autocorrelation and abnormal velocity patterns.
This is detectable.

Use case: real-time anomaly flagging, forgery detection,
structural integrity monitoring.

### Layer B — Canonical Lineage Verification

Clone discrimination requires a recorded canonical chain.

```
verifier records:  R_n at each step
clone produces:    R_n' ≠ R_n  (runtime entropy diverges immediately)
original produces: R_n  (matches recorded canonical value exactly)
```

canonical original match rate : 100%
canonical fork match rate     : 0%
first mismatch                : step 0 (immediately after fork)

Use case: identity continuity proof, lineage auditing,
existence verification over time.

