## 7. What IEPP Does and Does Not Claim

### Does claim:
- Structural attackers are detectable via statistical trajectory analysis
- Cloned trajectories diverge immediately and permanently from originals
- Canonical lineage verification provides definitive clone discrimination
- The three-layer verification structure (challenge binding,
  commitment chain, statistical continuity) provides layered defense

### Does not claim:
- Formal cryptographic proof of Trajectory Reconstruction Problem hardness
- Clone detection via statistical metrics alone
- Defense against Level 3 (infrastructure) or Level 4 (physical) adversaries
- Canonical selection — this is an application layer decision
- Governance of AI identity — this belongs to trust frameworks

